cs.CE, cs.NA, cs.MS, cs.CG, cs.ME 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the Finite Element Method (FEM) which is widely used in engineering applications. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper discusses the performance of different element types for a wide spectrum of elliptic PDEs. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is another possible category as the paper introduces a large set of benchmark problems and provides a reference implementation of their testing infrastructure. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possible category as the paper uses state-of-the-art meshing tools to create both unstructured and structured meshes. 
- cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the performance of different element types for static structural analysis and thermal analysis.
